  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "One example is Bitcoin, the world's first and most well-known blockchain network.",
    "Bitcoin uses a proof-of-work consensus mechanism, where miners compete to solve a complex algorithm to validate transactions and earn rewards.",
    "However, the concentration of mining power among a few large entities has been a concern for Bitcoin's governance (Nakamoto 2008).",
    "To address this, Bitcoin has implemented a mechanism called the \"difficulty adjustment\", which regulates the difficulty of the algorithm based on the total mining power on the network.",
    "This helps prevent any one entity from controlling the majority of the mining power, and thus maintaining the decentralisation of the network (Zhang et al. 2018b)."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
